#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.64"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.64:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.64:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.64:0.3"
msgid "64. Sīhanādasutta"
msgstr "64. The Lion’s Roar"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Chayimāni, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa tathāgatabalāni, yehi balehi samannāgato "
"tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, brahmacakkaṃ "
"pavatteti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, the Realized One possesses six powers of a Realized One. With "
"these he claims the bull’s place, roars his lion’s roar in the assemblies, "
"and turns the holy wheel."

msgctxt "an6.64:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.64:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato ṭhānañca ṭhānato aṭṭhānañca aṭṭhānato yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, the Realized One truly understands the possible as possible and the "
"impossible as impossible."

# Note that text here switches from yehi samannagato to yam agamma, a shift that appears to have been overlooked in BB’s translation.
msgctxt "an6.64:1.4"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgato ṭhānañca ṭhānato aṭṭhānañca aṭṭhānato "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, idampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa tathāgatabalaṃ hoti, "
"yaṃ balaṃ āgamma tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, parisāsu sīhanādaṃ "
"nadati, brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"Since he truly understands this, this is a power of the Realized One. "
"Relying on this he claims the bull’s place, roars his lion’s roar in the "
"assemblies, and turns the holy wheel."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato atītānāgatapaccuppannānaṃ "
"kammasamādānānaṃ ṭhānaso hetuso vipākaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the Realized One truly understands the result of deeds "
"undertaken in the past, future, and present in terms of causes and reasons."

msgctxt "an6.64:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgato atītānāgatapaccuppannānaṃ kammasamādānānaṃ "
"ṭhānaso hetuso vipākaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, idampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa "
"tathāgatabalaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, "
"parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti. (2)"
msgstr "Since he truly understands this, this is a power of the Realized One. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.418"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato jhānavimokkhasamādhisamāpattīnaṃ "
"saṅkilesaṃ vodānaṃ vuṭṭhānaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the Realized One truly understands corruption, cleansing, and "
"emergence regarding the absorptions, liberations, immersions, and "
"attainments."

msgctxt "an6.64:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgato … pe … idampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa "
"tathāgatabalaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, "
"parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti. (3)"
msgstr "Since he truly understands this, this is a power of the Realized One. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, "
"seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ, dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the Realized One recollects many kinds of past lives. That is: "
"one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a "
"thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, "
"many eons of the world evolving, many eons of the world contracting and "
"evolving. He remembers: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked "
"like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and "
"that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn "
"somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked "
"like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and "
"that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn "
"here.’ And so he recollects his many kinds of past lives, with features and "
"details."

msgctxt "an6.64:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgato anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, "
"seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ, dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, idampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa "
"tathāgatabalaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, "
"parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti. (4)"
msgstr "Since he truly understands this, this is a power of the Realized One. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, the Realized "
"One sees sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and "
"superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. He understands "
"how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds."

msgctxt "an6.64:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgato dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena …"
" pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti, idampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa "
"tathāgatabalaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, "
"parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti. (5)"
msgstr "Since he truly understands this, this is a power of the Realized One. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.419"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the Realized One has realized the undefiled freedom of heart "
"and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And he lives having realized it "
"with his own insight due to the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an6.64:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, bhikkhave, tathāgato āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"viharati, idampi, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa tathāgatabalaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ "
"āgamma tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, "
"brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti."
msgstr ""
"Since he truly understands this, this is a power of the Realized One. "
"Relying on this he claims the bull’s place, roars his lion’s roar in the "
"assemblies, and turns the holy wheel."

msgctxt "an6.64:6.3"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cha tathāgatassa tathāgatabalāni, yehi balehi "
"samannāgato tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, "
"brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"These are the six powers of a Realized One that the Realized One possesses. "
"With these he claims the bull’s place, roars his lion’s roar in the "
"assemblies, and turns the holy wheel."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:7.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ ṭhānañca ṭhānato aṭṭhānañca aṭṭhānato "
"yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena upasaṅkamitvā pañhaṃ pucchanti."
msgstr ""
"If others come to the Realized One and ask questions about his true "
"knowledge of the possible as possible and the impossible as impossible,"

msgctxt "an6.64:7.2"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa ṭhānañca ṭhānato aṭṭhānañca aṭṭhānato "
"yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ viditaṃ tathā tathā tesaṃ tathāgato ṭhānañca ṭhānato "
"aṭṭhānañca aṭṭhānato yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti. (1)"
msgstr "the Realized One answers them in whatever manner he has truly known it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:8.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannānaṃ "
"kammasamādānānaṃ ṭhānaso hetuso vipākaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena upasaṅkamitvā "
"pañhaṃ pucchanti."
msgstr ""
"If others come to the Realized One and ask questions about his true "
"knowledge of the result of deeds undertaken in the past, future, and present "
"in terms of causes and reasons,"

msgctxt "an6.64:8.2"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa atītānāgatapaccuppannānaṃ "
"kammasamādānānaṃ ṭhānaso hetuso vipākaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ viditaṃ tathā "
"tathā tesaṃ tathāgato atītānāgatapaccuppannānaṃ kammasamādānānaṃ ṭhānaso "
"hetuso vipākaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti. (2)"
msgstr "the Realized One answers them in whatever manner he has truly known it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:9.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ jhānavimokkhasamādhisamāpattīnaṃ "
"saṅkilesaṃ vodānaṃ vuṭṭhānaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena upasaṅkamitvā pañhaṃ "
"pucchanti."
msgstr ""
"If others come to the Realized One and ask questions about his true "
"knowledge of corruption, cleansing, and emergence regarding the absorptions, "
"liberations, immersions, and attainments,"

msgctxt "an6.64:9.2"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa jhānavimokkhasamādhisamāpattīnaṃ "
"saṅkilesaṃ vodānaṃ vuṭṭhānaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ viditaṃ tathā tathā tesaṃ "
"tathāgato jhānavimokkhasamādhisamāpattīnaṃ saṅkilesaṃ vodānaṃ vuṭṭhānaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti. (3)"
msgstr "the Realized One answers them in whatever manner he has truly known it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.420"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:10.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ pubbenivāsānussatiṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena "
"upasaṅkamitvā pañhaṃ pucchanti."
msgstr ""
"If others come to the Realized One and ask questions about his true "
"knowledge of recollection of past lives,"

msgctxt "an6.64:10.2"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa pubbenivāsānussatiṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ "
"viditaṃ tathā tathā tesaṃ tathāgato pubbenivāsānussatiṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena "
"pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti. (4)"
msgstr "the Realized One answers them in whatever manner he has truly known it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:11.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ sattānaṃ cutūpapātaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena "
"upasaṅkamitvā pañhaṃ pucchanti."
msgstr ""
"If others come to the Realized One and ask questions about his true "
"knowledge of passing away and rebirth of sentient beings,"

msgctxt "an6.64:11.2"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa sattānaṃ cutūpapātaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ "
"viditaṃ tathā tathā tesaṃ tathāgato sattānaṃ cutūpapātaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena "
"pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti. (5)"
msgstr "the Realized One answers them in whatever manner he has truly known it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:12.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra ce, bhikkhave, pare tathāgataṃ āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … yathābhūtaṃ "
"ñāṇena upasaṅkamitvā pañhaṃ pucchanti."
msgstr ""
"If others come to the Realized One and ask questions about his true "
"knowledge of the ending of defilements,"

msgctxt "an6.64:12.2"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ "
"viditaṃ tathā tathā tesaṃ tathāgato āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇena "
"pañhaṃ puṭṭho byākaroti. (6)"
msgstr "the Realized One answers them in whatever manner he has truly known it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
#. VAR: yampidaṃ → yamidaṃ (bj, pts1) | yadidaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.64:13.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yampidaṃ ṭhānañca ṭhānato aṭṭhānañca aṭṭhānato yathābhūtaṃ "
"ñāṇaṃ tampi samāhitassa vadāmi no asamāhitassa."
msgstr ""
"And I say that true knowledge of the possible as possible and the impossible "
"as impossible is for those with immersion, not for those without immersion."

#. VAR: Yampidaṃ → yadidaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.64:13.2"
msgid ""
"Yampidaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannānaṃ kammasamādānānaṃ ṭhānaso hetuso vipākaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ tampi samāhitassa vadāmi no asamāhitassa."
msgstr ""
"And true knowledge of the result of deeds undertaken in the past, future, "
"and present in terms of causes and reasons is for those with immersion, not "
"for those without immersion."

#. VAR: Yampidaṃ → yadidaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.64:13.3"
msgid ""
"Yampidaṃ jhānavimokkhasamādhisamāpattīnaṃ saṃkilesaṃ vodānaṃ vuṭṭhānaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ tampi samāhitassa vadāmi no asamāhitassa."
msgstr ""
"And true knowledge of corruption, cleansing, and emergence regarding the "
"absorptions, liberations, immersions, and attainments is for those with "
"immersion, not for those without immersion."

#. VAR: Yampidaṃ → yadidaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.64:13.4"
msgid ""
"Yampidaṃ pubbenivāsānussatiṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ tampi samāhitassa vadāmi no "
"asamāhitassa."
msgstr ""
"And true knowledge of the recollection of past lives is for those with "
"immersion, not for those without immersion."

#. VAR: Yampidaṃ → yadidaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.64:13.5"
msgid ""
"Yampidaṃ sattānaṃ cutūpapātaṃ yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ tampi samāhitassa vadāmi no "
"asamāhitassa."
msgstr ""
"And true knowledge of the passing away and rebirth of sentient beings is for "
"those with immersion, not for those without immersion."

#. VAR: Yampidaṃ → yadidaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.64:13.6"
msgid ""
"Yampidaṃ āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … yathābhūtaṃ ñāṇaṃ tampi samāhitassa vadāmi no "
"asamāhitassa."
msgstr ""
"And true knowledge of the ending of defilements is for those with immersion, "
"not for those without immersion."

msgctxt "an6.64:13.7"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, samādhi maggo, asamādhi kummaggo”ti."
msgstr ""
"And so, mendicants, immersion is the path. No immersion is the wrong path.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.64:13.8"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.64:13.9"
msgid "Mahāvaggo chaṭṭho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.421"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an6.64:14.1"
msgid "Soṇo phagguno bhijāti,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.64:14.2"
msgid "āsavā dāruhatthi ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.64:14.3"
msgid "Majjhe ñāṇaṃ nibbedhikaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.64:14.4"
msgid "sīhanādoti te dasāti."
msgstr ""
